rld-famous engineer (Rome, 10 AD)\n\n- Julius\n|\nI never meant it,' he was saying. 'Never meant it to happen. Can't stand it,seeing her suffer. Must do something, do something... What do I do? What can I do...?\n\n- Rachel Caine, Ghost Town\n|\nawake, then die in the arms of a modified lover sleep, then dream in the absence of a tangible lover envision, then sing in the thralls of a hungry lover\n\n- A.P. Sweet, The Abattoir of Silence\n|\nMany of the things that grownups have chosen to ignore, the child understands deeply.\n\n- R.\n|\nIf you want your inner light to shine brighter, illuminate someone else’s.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nAt the different stages of recognition, reflection, and redress, practicing compassion provides potentially world-saving opportunities which otherwise likely would not exist.\n\n- Aberjhani, Illuminated Corners: Collected Essays and Articles Volume I.\n|\nOnce you have endured sufferings, you can give someone strength.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nFathers, provoke not your children to wrath.\n\n- Fyodor Dostoyevsky, The Brothers Karamazov\n|\nThe way a man drinks in company tells you nothing about him, but the way he drinks when alone reveals, without his realizing it, the very depths of his soul.\n\n- Irène Némirovsky, Fire in the Blood\n|\nWith Ed, I always pushed away the good and only heard the bad. Today, I let in the good.\n\n- Jenni Schaefer, Goodbye Ed, Hello Me: Recover from Your Eating Disorder and Fall in Love with Life\n|\nYou know how it is -- you get older, you get wiser, you start to ask yourself 'is it any use being able to summon creatures of the nether deeps when I could be watching BBC 4?\n\n- Kate\n|\nTo me, the haircut represented beauty and strength, that I was a woman who would live her life without the boundaries imposed upon her by other people.\n\n- Kat Von D., Go Big or Go Home: Taking Risks in Life, Love, and Tattooing\n|\nIf the grass is greener on the other side of the fence, you can bet the water bill is higher.\n\n- Debbie Macomber, Mrs. Miracle\n|\nI want to make love, but my hair smells of war and running and running.\n\n- Warsan Shire, Teaching My Mother How to Give Birth\n|\nSome things are private. I mean, we're grown-ups now. You don't share everything.\n\n- Sophie Kinsella, Shopaholic to the Rescue\n|\nIf I had not try and taken chances, I would have miss many opportunities in life.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nSome say I'm an overnight success. Well, that was a very long night that lasted about 10 years.\n\n- Lisa\n|\nTo be alone is to be different, to be different is to be alone.\n\n- Suzanne\n|\nTo the real artist in humanity, what are called bad manners are often the most picturesque and significant of all.\n\n- Walt\n|\nI am the happiest person on this world, who has never seen ups and downs in life. I got whatever I wished for… And I woke up!\n\n- Rahul Rampal, Notorious Mind- Just Engaged\n|\nLove is the essence, fragrance, and beauty of life.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nyou find yourself repeating, ‘They grow up so quickly, don’t they?’ when all you really mean is: time goes faster for me nowadays.\n\n- Julian Barnes, The Sense of an Ending\n|\nA writer, like a sheriff, is the embodiment of a group of people and without their support both are in a tight spot.\n\n- Craig Johnson, Another Man's Moccasins\n|\nGod never gives you more than you can handle. It's your choice on how you deal with what he gives you. You can either grow from it, or you can lie down and give up.\n\n- Kendra\n|\nMy mission in life is to be kind, compassionate, caring, sharing and loving in order to feel the deepest joy of life.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI wanted to feel less.To not be burdened by emotion,To not feel sadness,To not know loss.I envied the inanimate,The trees that stand proudly in winter,Not missing their leaves.\n\n- Jacqueline\n|\nIf Strength comes through Suffering, why then I should be the strongest of all women, yet I am the weakest. God help me. Help me.\n\n- Lee Sm